@tuukkamustonen yes, bumpversion is not for every setup.

If you have a single point of truth (e.g. git's tags or a single file) for versions, then there's less need for `bumpversion`. Also, if you don't need to increment versions headless (say, e.g. in a contiuous integration environment by the press of a button), you can just do the computation in your head and do stuff manually.

