@rafaelsilverioit another couple of tips if I may:
* no need to add the `.patch` file to the code repository
* try working in a separate branch (call it "keep-pb2-suffix" for example), add the changes to the new branch and send pull request from that branch, not from your master branch, this is the recommended practice in git. This way you keep your master branch clean and you can easily fast-forward it if needed when the upstream updates their master branch.

What is the best behavior for getting a component? Should all aliases return one of the other aliases if it does not exist?

For example:

    @property
    def city(self):
        city = self.parse['components'].get('city')
        if city:
            return city
        elif self.town:
            return self.town
        elif self.village:
            return self.village
        elif self.county:
            return self.county

Will return the town if city does not exist, but:

    @property
    def town(self):
        return self.parse['components'].get('town')

will only return the town if it exists. Should it be changed to:

    @property
    def city_aliases(self):
        town = self.parse['components'].get('town')
        city = self.parse['components'].get('town')
        village = self.parse['components'].get('town')
        county = self.parse['components'].get('town')
        if city:
            return city
        elif town :
            return town 
        elif village:
            return village
        elif county:
            return county

    @property
    def city(self):
        city = self.parse['components'].get('city')
        if city:
            return city
        else:
            return self.city_aliases

