In case anybody else is looking at this, the django documentation on field access API is helpful: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.9/ref/models/meta/#field-access-api

Instead of Version.content_type.model_class()._meta.fields and Version.content_type.model_class()._meta.many_to_many you can use Version.content_type.model_class()._meta.get_fields() to get all fields (including fk and m2m). And Version.content_type.model_class()._meta.get_field() can be used to get a field by name.

So if `version` is a `reversion.models.Version`, I can get what I want by doing something like:
```
for k,v in version.field_dict.iteritems():
    field = version.content_type.model_class()._meta.get_field(k)
    if type(field) is models.ManyToManyField:
        # loop through k, using each list entry as a primary key to objects using the field.related_model model
    elif type(field) is models.ForeignKey:
        # more or less the same thing as with m2m, but only one value!
    else:
        # the field isn't a relation, so probably just give the value to the user in its current state.
```

