@kc64 Thanks for your review. Unfortunately I'm not experienced enough with ZMQ to comment. This code was contributed, and as it is committed I have verified works fine. If you can propose a way to eliminate the broker, I would be interested in that.

> the more important part is the use of PUB rather than PUSH. PUSH will distribute requests unequally among PULLers while a PUB on bind will distribute equally among all SUBs.

As I said above, I did not write this code, but I'm not sure your comment applies, since the PUSH/PULL connection is always a one-to-one. The broker script is a publisher, and all the server nodes are subscribers, and also have a pull/push connection to the broker, though which they send to the broker what needs to be published. The structure makes sense to me, but if you can propose a better way, I would definitely consider it.

